  "description": "<p>分类: <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/wearables/\" rel=\"tag\">佩戴产品</a></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/06/27/foxconn-demos-iphone-friendly-smartwatch-that-shows-messages-and/\"><img src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/cn.engadget.com/media/2013/06/hon-hai-smartwatch.jpg\" style=\"margin: 4px;\" /></a></div>\n\n<div><br />\n那边厢传说中的 <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/02/10/nyt-apple-experimenting-with-wrist-worn-ios-devices-using-curved-glass/\">iWatch</a> 还没有登场亮相，这一边苹果的老朋友<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/tag/foxconn\">富士康</a>就迫不及待地拿出了一款由自己打造的智能手表。据悉这款产品可用于和 iPhone 相连，能被用来预览通话及 Facebook 信息。除此之外，它还具备了健康监测功能，用户可以拿它来追踪自己的呼吸和心跳频率。据称未来富士康还考虑为其加入指纹扫描器，以此来确认个人健康数据的安全。至于发售信息的话目前还依然成谜，总的来说，其象徵意义要比产品本身来得更为重要。毕竟和只会接单生产的代工厂相比，善於开发新品的企业听上去要好很多吧。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n经由：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2013/06/27/foxconn-demos-iphone-friendly-smartwatch-that-shows-messages-and/\">engadget</a><br />\n引用来源：<a href=\"http://www.wantchinatimes.com/news-subclass-cnt.aspx?id=20130627000079&amp;cid=1206\" target=\"_blank\">Want ChinaTimes</a></div><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/06/27/foxconn-demos-iphone-friendly-smartwatch-that-shows-messages-and/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20641035/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/06/27/foxconn-demos-iphone-friendly-smartwatch-that-shows-messages-and/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
